text: @FedExHelp My fiancé drove 40 mins out of the way to your main processing facility to go pick up a package that could have easily been dropped off at our building’s front desk.

@FedExHelp  Now no one wants to do their job and grab the package because it’s in a trailer that’s “impossible” to get because there’s too many packages. 

You’re a shipping company. There should be a easy process and your employees should be willing to help a customer.
@FedExHelp The woman is not helpful and feeding the same “impossible” excuse to other guests walking in.
@jessaza_ Hi Jessica, this is Chalisse. I would like to check into this for you.  Please DM your name, delivery address, tracking number and phone number. Thank you
